JOHANNESBURG – ANC in Gauteng will held a state of readiness briefing for their conference happening this weekend. Acting Provincial Chairperson David Makhura will be going through issues of policy, which is likely to dominate deliberations in Irene, Tshwane. We will on Monday, 16 July 2018 brief the media on our state of readiness to hold the 13th Provincial Conference which is taking place on 20 to 22 July 2018 at St George Hotel, Irene in Tshwane Makhura is expected to be elected chairperson after Paul Mashatile was elected national treasurer at the ANC's elective conference in December last year. The provincial conferences of the ANC have been marred by court actions from disgruntled members within the party. eNCA